{"source_key":"sha256-c55db1afbbe5d9067606af4f013482ee","record_index":898,"record_hash":"sha256:9589a9d71806658cf8648a2d3254e3c3368ace799dc805ceec1a0cd27e83437f","timestamp":"2026-05-31T12:59:21.827Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n- [P2] `MetaMove` is `#[non_exhaustive]`, but its struct variants are still directly constructible by downstream crates, so adding fields later is breaking. Since constructors already exist, mark `KeyPrefix` and `SetMembers` variants `#[non_exhaustive]` too. Same deal for returned `MoveStats`: add `#[non_exhaustive]` or keep fields private. Refs: [types.rs:392]([REDACTED:path]), [types.rs:437]([REDACTED:path])\\n\\n- [P2] Duplicate `SetMembers` input fails the whole move: `[\\\"s1\\\", \\\"s1\\\"]` adds/upserts twice, removes once, then the second remove returns `ValueNotFound` and rolls back. For a set-member API this should dedupe and count unique moved members, or reject duplicates during preflight with a clear typed error. Refs: [types.rs:407]([REDACTED:path]), [moves.rs:259]([REDACTED:path])\\n\\n- [P2] Move-specific conflicts are currently stringly `InvalidValue`s, so callers can’t distinguish “destination exists” from “generated duplicate destination” without parsing messages. This is a new public API surface; add a typed error shape now, even if it’s one generic move-conflict variant with a reason. Refs: [moves.rs:114]([REDACTED:path]), [moves.rs:129]([REDACTED:path])\\n\\n- [P3] Public docs don’t say what `apply_moves` can return as errors. Add a short `# Errors` section covering invalid/overlapping prefixes, destination collisions, source key/type/member failures, and rollback semantics. Refs: [session_handle.rs:203]([REDACTED:path]), [types.rs:388]([REDACTED:path])\\n\\n**Taste-only ignored**\\n- I’d ignore changing `&[String]` to a fancier generic member input for